column5: Just got back from Quinte. Great weather and fishing. 6 guys. The last day, 1 guy had to go home so we fished in my boat 5 guys, what a hoot  . at times we had 8 lines out, all off plainers and flat lines. Last count was 28 fish. 3 to 12 lbs. bait was Stretch 20, Tail Dancers, Reef Runners, in different colours. I wish you all could have as good as weather we had, we'll never have weather like that agian in Nov.. 3 days in a row. A few pictures to share This is the Gang                                       And of course, my mug shot
Great report and great eyes!!! Looked like an awesome time for you guys.  I made it out there on Sunday as well....what a perfect weather day....who knows, I may have seen you out there.
Nice work out there FF  Sherriff
Great stuff FF ! 5 in the boat must have been "busy"!
Congrats on a great trip. Geez, 5 guys and 8 rods, must have been pretty busy indeed when somebody hooked up!  Mike
Nice Fish Guys    Wow Mirror smooth water on Quinte in Nov  ,,, dont see that to often.    Hope no one got a sheepy with all those lines out ..that could have been a real mess.
boat looks well rigged for the job  great report
well done FF thats a busy looking porcupine of a boat if ive ever seen one!
Great pictures.  Beauty weather.  You all did great.  Very Jealous.
Nice going FF, looks like you and the boys had a great time.  I'll be heading up there next weekend, but it looks like I won't be getting the weather you guys had unfortunately.
Just Awesome.  What a set up you got there.  Joey
Great job FF. Looks like a busy boat but probably alot of fun. Thanks for the report.  Mike
Fishfarmer,Nice 3 days bud with some sweet looking eye,s to boot WTG. The guy in the fourth pic is that who I think it is,and he caught a fish LOL.  Steve
Thanks everyone. Yes Steve, thats Cookie. I think he caught the biggest fish.
NIce report, all I can say is I am jealous
Im jealous also,  Party on a boat catching enormous eyes. Priceless!!  nice report, Thanks!!
Great pictures FF, always nice to get days like that in November!
That musta been a great trip, thanks for sharing...
